title: BAP Candidate Nawabzada Tariq Magsi wins PB-11 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Balochistan Awami Party (BAP) candidate Nawabzada Tariq Magsi has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-11, Jhall Magsi by securing 44,556 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner up was Balochistan National Party (BNP) candidate Mir Murtaza Abbas who bagged 1,244 votes.
Overall voters turn out remained 67.96 per cent.
